<DOC><DOCNO> AP880213-0052 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-13-88 0539EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Philippines-Prison     02-13 0156</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Philippines-Prison,0162</SECOND><HEAD>Eight Inmates Bolt Prison</HEAD><DATELINE>ZAMBOANGA CITY, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Eight convicts armed withknives and homemade bombs escaped from a southern penal colony bytaking hostage the penitentiary's superintendent and his wife,police said today.   The hostages were released later.   Most of the escapees are serving terms for murder.   Police said the inmates barged into the chapel of the San RamonPrison and Penal Farm and seized superintendent Leonito Narvaez andhis wife as the couple attended Mass late Friday with other prisonofficials and prisoners.   The inmates then walked out the gates of the sprawling complex,threatening to kill the hostages if guards tried to stop them,police said.   Narvaez and his wife were released two hours later in a villageseveral miles away.   Most inmates at the penal colony, near Zamboanga City 540 milessoutheast of Manila, live with their families and are allowed tocultivate small farms within the complex.</TEXT></DOC>